{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"322","heading":"Federal Government service delivery","label":"322 Federal Government service delivery","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/ptI/ch3/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—1So in original. No subsec. (b) has been enacted.1Federal Government Service Delivery Lead","label":"a .—1So in original. No subsec. (b) has been enacted.1Federal Government Service Delivery Lead","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Facilitate and coordinate governmentwide efforts to improve Government service delivery provided by agencies, particularly with respect to high impact service providers.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Carry out the duties and powers prescribed by the Director.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Serve as the lead, governmentwide official responsible for supporting Government service delivery.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Advise the Director concerning the improvement of Government service delivery provided by agencies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"understand the needs of an individual, business, or organization interacting with an agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"solicit and consider voluntary feedback on the Government service delivery by the agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"assess Government service delivery processes;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"consider the factors of ease, efficiency, transparency, accessibility, fairness, burden (as defined in ), and duration, including wait and processing times, with respect to Government service delivery; andsection 3502 of title 44","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F5%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"encourage the adoption of commercial products and services in accordance with .section 3307 of title 41","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Collect and report qualitative and quantitative information or data on Government service delivery through existing reporting mechanisms.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Evaluate the quality of Government service delivery, including through the establishment of performance metrics developed using the standards, policies, and guidelines developed pursuant to paragraph (5) and the information or data collected and reported pursuant to paragraph (6).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Engage with stakeholders to identify leading practices in service design and delivery that would improve Government service delivery across and within agencies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":null,"label":"9","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Ensure agency service delivery initiatives, including those related to the 21st Century Integrated Digital Experience Act ( note; ), are identified in agency congressional budget justifications.15 U.S.C. 3501Public Law 115–336","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":null,"label":"10","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Coordinate with Office of Management and Budget stakeholders and other agency stakeholders on Government service delivery.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":null,"label":"11","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s322/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs322%2Fa%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In collaboration with relevant agency officials as appropriate, and in coordination with relevant Office of Management and Budget stakeholders, ensure that websites of agencies, including those associated with high impact service providers, are consistent with the objectives of this subchapter, the 21st Century Integrated Digital Experience Act, and any other applicable law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
